cat: Display contect of files
sudo:  Super user
grep: Globally search and print. search specific string
head: Fisrt 10 lines of file
tail: Last 10 lines
logger: Add entries in     /var/log/syslog  
journalctl: Display log entries from several sources
chmod: Change mod. R,W,X  ; file owner, owner group, everyone else 



Networking

ping: Test network connectivity by sending ICMP echo requests to a host.
traceroute: Trace the route taken by packets from the source to the destination host.
netstat: Display network connections and routing tables.
ifconfig: Configure network interfaces and display network configuration.
ip: Configure and display network interfaces, routing tables, and network settings.
route: Configure and display routing tables.
arp: Display and modify the Address Resolution Protocol (ARP) cache.
tcpdump: Capture and analyze network traffic.
dig: Perform DNS lookups and display information about DNS servers and domains.
nslookup: Perform DNS lookups and display information about DNS servers and domains.
host: Perform DNS lookups and display information about DNS servers and domains.
nmap: Scan for open ports and detect network vulnerabilities.
iptables: Configure the Linux firewall.
ssh: Connect to a remote host using the Secure Shell (SSH) protocol.
scp: Securely copy files between hosts using the SSH protocol.
rsync: Efficiently synchronize files between hosts.
wget: Download files from the Internet using HTTP, HTTPS, and FTP protocols.
curl: Transfer data from or to a server using various protocols, including HTTP, HTTPS, and FTP.
iftop: Display network traffic in real-time.
iptraf: Monitor network traffic in real-time and analyze network statistics.
mtr: Network diagnostic tool that combines the functionality of ping and traceroute.
ss: Display detailed information about network sockets and connections.
hostname: Display or set the hostname of the Linux system.
netstat: Print network connections, routing tables, interfaces statistics, masquerade connections and multicast memberships.
route-nop: Display routing tables in numeric format.
ifup/ifdown: Bring network interfaces up or down.
